devdoc.details: A smart contract for registering and managing land ownership on the blockchain.

LandForSale(uint256,address).details: Emitted when a land plot is put up for sale by its owner.

params.id: The ID of the land listed for sale.
params.owner: The Ethereum address of the owner listing the land.

LandRegistered(uint256,address,string,st.details: Emitted when a new land plot is successfully registered.

params.id: The unique ID of the registered land.
params.owner: The Ethereum address of the initial owner.

LandTransferred(uint256,address,address).details: Emitted when the ownership of a land plot is successfully transferred.

params.from: The Ethereum address of the previous owner.
params.id: The ID of the transferred land.
params.to: The Ethereum address of the new owner.

TransferApproved(uint256,address).details: Emitted when the owner approves a pending transfer request.

params.id: The ID of the land whose transfer was approved.
params.newOwner: The Ethereum address of the new owner after approval.

TransferDenied(uint256,address).details: Emitted when the owner denies a pending transfer request.

params.id: The ID of the land whose transfer was denied.
params.requester: The Ethereum address of the user whose transfer request was denied.

TransferRequested(uint256,address).details: Emitted when a user requests a transfer of a land plot that is for sale.

params.id: The ID of the land for which a transfer is requested.
params.requester: The Ethereum address of the user requesting the transfer.

approveTransfer(uint256).details: Allows the owner of a land plot to approve a pending transfer request. Only the owner of the land can call this function, and a transfer request must be pending.

params._landId: The ID of the land for which to approve the transfer.

constructor.details: Constructor to initialize the contract. Sets the initial land count to zero. The admin address is initialized directly with the constant.

denyTransfer(uint256).details: Allows the owner of a land plot to deny a pending transfer request. Only the owner of the land can call this function, and a transfer request must be pending.

params._landId: The ID of the land for which to deny the transfer.

getAllLands().details: Allows the admin to retrieve details of all registered land plots.

returns._0: An array of Land structs containing details of all registered lands.

getLandsByOwner(address).details: Returns an array of land IDs owned by a specific address.

params._owner: The Ethereum address of the owner.

returns._0: An array of uint256 representing the IDs of the lands owned by the address.

getPastOwnershipDetails(uint256).details: Allows the admin to retrieve the ownership history of a specific land plot.

params._landId: The ID of the land to retrieve the ownership history for.

returns._0: An array of OwnershipHistory structs representing the past owners and timestamps.

getPendingTransferRequests(address).details: Returns an array of land IDs owned by a specific address that have pending transfer requests.

params._owner: The Ethereum address of the owner.

returns._0: An array of uint256 representing the IDs of the lands with pending transfer requests.

putLandForSale(uint256).details: Allows the owner of a land plot to mark it as being for sale. Only the owner of the land can call this function.

params._landId: The ID of the land to put up for sale.

registerLand(string,string,string,string.details: Registers a new land plot in the registry. Only users can call this function to register land they own.

params._areaSqYd: The area of the land in square yards.
params._plotNumber: The official plot number of the land.

requestTransfer(uint256).details: Allows a user to request a transfer of a land plot that is for sale. The land must be marked as for sale, and no other transfer request should be pending. The requester cannot be the current owner.

params._landId: The ID of the land for which a transfer is requested.
